title: Texas Firm Recalls Beef and Pork Products Produced Without Benefit of Inspection and Misbranding
summary: WASHINGTON, Oct. 15, 2012 - Lao Chareune Foods, a Dallas, Texas, establishment, is recalling approximately 8,200 pounds of various beef and pork products because they were produced without the benefit of federal inspection and misbranded, the U.S. Department of Agriculture's Food Safety and Inspection Service...
